<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News service for Friday, June 12. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
TOURISM (Phoenix) - Phoenix is a sweltering, barren desert devoid
of culture, activities and excitement. That's what many who have
never visited the Valley of the Sun said when asked for their
impressions of our fair city, according to the bureau responsible
forpromoting tourism in Phoenix. So the Phoenix and Valley of the
Sun Convention and Visitors Bureau has decided to change its name,
logo and marketing strategy. By CRAIG ANDERSON. Story will move in
the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
NOISE (Phoenix) - Nearly nine out of 10 planes flying in and out of
Sky Harbor International Airport meet federal standards for quieter
engines, but that hasn't stopped people from complaining about the
noise. Airport authorities say 86 percent of the fleet has already
met the quiet standard, which is mandatory as of Jan. 1, 2000.
Residents under the airport's flight path, though, say they haven't
noticed a descending hush. By MARY JO PITZL. Story will move in the
``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
