<HEADER>
A6225 &Cx1f; tad-z
r t &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ORLANDO-BNB13-COX     06-12 0335
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ORLANDO-BNB13-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    B&AMP;B Courts the past, pampers guests
 &HT;    Sidebar to ORLANDO1
 &HT;    By Loretta Grantham
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ORLANDO, Fla. _ Although The Courtyard at Lake Lucerne is
virtually under the East-West Expressway _ and within walking
distance of downtown _ you won't hear a thing. Maybe it's the
thick-walled construction of yesteryear.
</P>
<P>
   The bed-and-breakfast is a trio of buildings that includes the
Norment-Parry Inn, Orlando's oldest house (built in 1883) with six
rooms each decorated by a different designer (you'll love the pink
and green Baby's Room); the Wellborn Building, Art Deco suites with
period furniture, such as a zebra-print sofa; and the I.W. Phillips
House, which has French doors, a wraparound veranda and a baby
grand piano.
</P>
<P>
   Antiques are everywhere.
</P>
<P>
   Just outside is sidewalk-lined Lake Lucerne (schedule a few
laps) and the Lake Cherokee Historic District, filled with stately
homes dating from the mid-1880s.
</P>
<P>
   A breakfast buffet is served each morning (no lunch or dinner),
plus a bottle of wine greets guests upon arrival.
</P>
<P>
   Chill out in a porch swing, a claw-foot bathtub or an
overstuffed chintz chair. This is definitely the slow lane (but
conveniently close to the fast lane).
</P>
<P>
   Directions: Take Florida's Turnpike to Interstate 4 East. Exit
at Anderson Street, and turn right. Continue through next three
lights and turn right onto Delaney Avenue. Take the first right
onto Lucerne Circle North.
</P>
<P>
   Rates: Norment-Parry Victorian rooms, $85-$119; Wellborn
one-bedroom suites, $109, and honeymoon suite, $150; I.W. Phillips
Edwardian suites, $120-$165. Rates are single or double occupancy.
</P>
<P>
   In each room: TV, telephone, clock radio, private bath.
</P>
<P>
   Note: The Courtyard isn't geared for kids under 12. Teens are
allowed in Wellborn suites for an additional $15 per night. No
pets.
</P>
<P>
   Contact: (407) 648-5188 or (800) 444-5289.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
