<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S BUSINESS EVENTS CALENDAR  
(FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, JUNE 14)
</HEADLINE>
  (af) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONDAY: The Agriculture Department reports on 1998 crop
conditions for wheat, corn, soybeans and cotton.
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY: The Labor Department releases the Consumer Price Index
for May. An increase of 0.2 percent is expected.
</P>
<P>
   The Commerce Department reports on May housing starts. An
increase to 1.447 million is expected.
</P>
<P>
   The Federal Reserve reports on May industrial production, which
is expected to rise 0.4 percent, and capacity utilization, which is
expected to edge up 0.1 percentage point, to 82 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Alan Greenspan, chairman of the Federal Reserve, and other
government officials are to testify before the Senate Judiciary
Committee on mergers and the economy.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY: The Federal Reserve releases its Beige Book report on
regional economic prospects.
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY: The Commerce Department reports on the international
trade balance for April. A deficit of $13 billion is expected.
</P>
<P>
   FRIDAY: The Treasury Department releases its May budget
statement. A $40 billion deficit is expected. &QL;
</P>
