<P>
   &QL; 
MCCAIN-JOKE (Phoenix) - Sen. John McCain formally apologized to
President Clinton Friday for a crude joke he made earlier in the
week involving the first lady, her daughter and Attorney General
Janet Reno. ``He feels terrible that he said it,'' McCain press
aide Nancy Ives said. The joke was so bad that Ives declined to
repeat it. ``I don't feel comfortable telling you the joke,'' she
said. ``He feels awful and he regrets that he said it . . . I just
can't repeat it.'' But The Republic has learned it goes something
like this: Do you know why Chelsea is so ugly? Because Janet Reno
is her father. It's the latest in a string of eyebrow-raising
gaffes by the man who many consider a likely White House 2000
candidate. Remember Seizure World? By MICHAEL MURPHY. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MEXHOTELS (HERMOSILLO, Sonora) _ The Mexicans call them hoteles de
paso, rather luxurious rental units behind high compound walls with
mirrors, soft music and European porno channels, for those quickly
passing through. Well, you've got the idea. They are used primarily
by Mexican men and their numerous lovers on the side. And, while
the prevailing thought in Mexico is that machismo is a way of life
that
</P>
<P>
   has declined in popularity in recent years, there has been a
building boom recently in Hermosillo of the hotels. There are now
six of them on the outskirts of the city. What a change from a
decade ago when the first one, the Hotel El Cid, was built, raising
a firestorm of criticism from the proper citizens of the Sonoran
capitol. BY MARK SHAFFER. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
