By PAT KOSSAN. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
LOTTERY (Phoenix) - Ruth Wennerlund, like many regular
Lotteryplayers, uses familiar numbers when she purchases tickets.
Her son was born on Sept. 7, so she always bought Pick 3 tickets
with the same three numbers: 9-0-7. But after a month of playing
the popular new game, she noticed something odd. The number 9 never
was selected during the nightly computer drawings for the game.
``It was really strange,'' said Wennerlund, a Chandler resident.
``So on Tuesday I decided to call the Lottery and ask why 9 had
never been picked.'' Wennerlund said she was told that Lottery
officials had carefully examined the game and that there were no
problems. So she was understandably surprised Friday morning when
she read in ``The Arizona Republic'' that the game had been
suspended because a computer glitch had left nines out of the
drawings. ``I was just so mad,'' said Wennerlund. By HAL MATTERN.
Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
