<P>
   (Revised) CLINTON-DEVELOPING _ WASHINGTON _ On June 24 President
Clinton heads to China for the third of this year's five planned
presidential forays into the developing world. The 10-day China
visit, an extraordinary amount of time for a single country, comes
on the heels of Clinton's Africa trip in March and his visit to
South America in April. (Deans, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving Tuesday, June 9 in both the (i) International and
(k) Commentary categories for use Sunday, June 14.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-PEASANTS _ GUO YUAN, China _ Gazing down over green rice
shoots that forever have been the Chinese peasant's sweaty handhold
on life, Zhan Hanjuin couldn't dismiss the broad grin that had
played across his face all afternoon. It was hard for him still to
believe he was standing atop his own new, two-story house with a
fish pond on the roof, a Volkswagen Santana in the garage, and a
six-foot-high air conditioner in the parlor. (Kunstel, Cox News
Service).
</P>
<P>
   (New). With PEASANTS-MAO _ SHAOSHAN, China _ The adobe house
where Mao Tse-tung grew up is a shrine not just to the father of
communist China, but to the spirit of the peasants who inspired and
helped him fight a revolution. (Kunstel, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving Tuesday, June 9, for use Saturday, June 14.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-BRIDES _ KRASNOYARSK, Russia _ In the world of lonely
hearts, Tatyana Denoshova's lament rings loud and often: ``It's
difficult to meet a real man here. Good men are already married and
if they are not already married, they are no good.'' In her case,
though, the desperation resonates with urgency. A 25-year-old
hospital nurse in this depressed Siberia city, Denoshova earns only
$40 a month and hasn't been paid since March. She says the men she
meets are similarly strapped, or sodden with vodka, or both. She
and thousands of other Russian women have turned to mail-order,
video and Internet-based matchmaking services seeking husbands _
preferably American or European men who will love them and take
them far away from the dead-end of today's Russia. (Holmes). EDs:
Moving Thursday, June 11, for use Saturday, June 14.
</P>
