that fail to hire enough blacks and Latinos from bringing in
temporary foreign workers. By Julia Angwin
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SOUP _ &LR;  Ever notice those little milk cartons sitting next to
the spinach fettuccine in the cold-food section of the supermarket?
</P>
<P>
   Ever wonder why milk cartons were sitting next to the spinach
fettuccine in the cold-food section of the supermarket?
</P>
<P>
   If so, you can understand the challenge faced by Glencoe Foods
Inc., a company with British roots that plans a major U.S. roll-out
of fresh-prepared soups sold in pint-sized, white cartons. By Carol
Emert
