<HEADLINE>
COMPANY NEWS 
(HLW) 
</HEADLINE>
  c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Delphi Financial Group Inc., Wilmington, Del., agreed to buy
Matrix Absence Management Inc., San Jose, Calif., a privately held
company that provides disability services to employers, for an
undisclosed combination of stock, cash and notes.
</P>
<P>
   Greif Bros Corp., Delaware, Ohio, a maker of paper and metal
shipping containers, said it would take a third-quarter charge of
$27.5 million to close 18 plants and sell some assets as it
streamlines operations after an acquisition.
</P>
</TEXT>
