<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Earnhardt, McReynolds: no chemistry
 &HT;    By Tom McCollister
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   BROOKLYN, Mich. _ ``We could have let the truck driver set it up
at Richmond and not made a difference.''
</P>
<P>
   With those words, Larry McReynolds put into perspective what
went wrong with his tenure as crew chief for driver Dale Earnhardt.
It didn't work.
</P>
<P>
   When the Winston Cup garage opened Friday morning at Michigan
Speedway, McReynolds was guiding operations for Mike Skinner and
Kevin Hamlin was heading Earnhardt's efforts, a crew chief switch
made earlier in the week by owner Richard Childress.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everybody looks for that elusive chemistry,'' McReynolds said.
``We didn't have it. After the (Daytona) 500, for both teams, it's
been like an avalanche we haven't been able to stop.''
</P>
<P>
   McReynolds admits that one of his problems may have been forcing
too much information on Earnhardt.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm so intense that during qualifying I would go stand down in
the first corner and radio Dale that `we're off (in speed) because
we're not on gas here.' The feeling I got was I'm not sure he
wanted to know what I was telling him.''
</P>
<P>
   Earnhardt Jr. deal
</P>
<P>
   Dale Earnhardt Jr. was assured job security for the next five
years Friday when he agreed to a long-term deal with Dale Earnhardt
Incorporated, with options for five additional years. The younger
Earnhardt plans to continue in NASCAR's Busch series for the
remainder of the '98 season and as well as the entire '99 campaign.
``It feels good to finally have a formal contract signed with Dale
Jr.,'' said Earnhardt Sr. ``But our blood contract has been good
for 23 years.''
</P>
<P>
   Gerhardt on pole:
</P>
<P>
   Bobby Gerhardt won the pole Friday for today's ARCA 200 with a
single lap time of 180.768 miles per hour. Second fastest was Gary
Laton at 178.191. One of Gerhardt's sponsors is the Knight Ridder
newspaper chain.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
