   BC-FAT-SUBSTITUTE-FLAWS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, June 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June
10, about the possible health risks of olestra, the new fat
substitute, referred incompletely to the position of a Food and
Drug Administration advisory committee. While it appears that
olestra will remain on the market, Dr. Alan Rulis, director of the
office of premarket approval in the Center for Food Safety and
Applied Nutrition, said in an interview: ``I don't want to prejudge
the issue. It is far from settled, but we have not seen real
documented consensus agreement about the benefits of carotenoids.
The regulatory status of olestra will be status quo.''
</P>
<P>
   BC-HOBOKEN-CROONER-NYT (moved on Wednesday, June 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June
10, misstated the title of a song recorded by the singer Jimmy
Roselli. It is ``Mala Femmina.'' (``Bad Woman'' is the
translation.)
</P>
