<HEADLINE>
ON SEAU, HIDEO AND VIDEO
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By KEVIN MODESTI  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Lies, damned lies and statistics:
</P>
<P>
   Just the Lakers' luck. (begin ital)Now(end ital) the Utah Jazz
stops scoring.
</P>
<P>
   It must be luck, right? Because Del Harris did quote the stats
that showed the Lakers had one of the NBA's best defenses....
</P>
<P>
   Magic Johnson knows he's unqualified to host a late-night talk
show. But it's something to do until he runs for the Senate....
</P>
<P>
   That slogan, ``We Got Next,'' with its
grammatical-rules-breaking, anti-establishment flavor, really
captures the spirit of the WNBA _ a plucky, shoestring enterprise
making its way in the sports world on sheer guts and guile, facing
nothing but resistance from other basketball leagues and from
corporate America, without the benefit of a single
network-television promo to ram the idea down our throats....
</P>
<P>
   All this worry about the future of American literature and then
along comes ``The Quotable ESPN'' (introduction by Charles
Barkley)....
</P>
<P>
   The Clippers must build through the draft. If they try to
improve too fast, they could screw everything up....
</P>
<P>
   When you tire of the complexities of pro sports, there's always
the College World Series, baseball in its purest form....
</P>
<P>
   Junior Seau made the kind of sacrifice a team leader must make
when he cut short a vacation to report to Chargers training
camp....
</P>
<P>
   With the Hideo Nomo trade, all the sunshine went out of the
Dodgers clubhouse....
</P>
<P>
   Watching the Fox Group deal with disgruntled players, you wonder
in retrospect, how big a mistake was not trading Koufax and
Drysdale in 1966?
</P>
<P>
   Then again, you can't argue with the results of the recent
trades. If the Dodgers keep winning at their post-Piazza pace, and
the Giants and Padres keep winning at their season-long pace, the
Dodgers will finish within 14 games of first place....
</P>
<P>
   Look up ``class'' in the dictionary, and you'll find a picture
of Hideo Nomo....
</P>
<P>
   When I see that our sports cartoonist dislikes soccer, I worry
about the future of the sport.
</P>
<P>
   Nothing but 0-0 games _ that's why the World Cup is dying.
</P>
<P>
   If you hate soccer, please don't hesitate to tell everybody,
because your opinion matters.
</P>
<P>
   Strong pregame show on the 5:30 a.m. Paraguay-Bulgaria match.
</P>
<P>
   Hearing the ESPN announcers match language and insight with
their British partners makes you proud to be an American....
</P>
<P>
   Without baseball's interleague play, an intense regional rivalry
like Houston-Detroit never would have been developed....
</P>
<P>
   It's hard to get excited about the Stanley Cup Finals when the
Kings aren't involved....
</P>
<P>
   What makes Lee Hamilton so likable is his sincerity. ``Thanks
for calling. Have yourself a good evening. You call again.'' Some
radio guys, if they said things like that, would sound like they're
just filling the dead air while they punch up the next caller....
</P>
<P>
   A thought for bodybuilding-magazine publishers: Why not try
exploiting the sex appeal of female fitness competitors?...
</P>
<P>
   No fair laughing at Randy Johnson's appearance. He does the best
he can with it....
</P>
<P>
   What rips the heart out of a boxing fan is when a fight like
Holyfield-Akinwande finally gets made and then it has to be
canceled....
</P>
<P>
   When it comes to sports broadcasters, give me the wisdom of guys
who played the game, like Isiah Thomas and Rick Monday, over guys
who didn't, like Bob Costas and Vin Scully....
</P>
<P>
   Bravo to ESPN (The Magazine) for never letting style get in the
way of substance....
</P>
<P>
   Sure, sluggers like Mark McGwire and Juan Gonzalez are flashy,
but give me a lineup full of .300 hitters like Brett Butler any
day....
</P>
<P>
   Casey Martin can win the U.S. Open with any kind of racing
luck....
</P>
<P>
   What makes Yankee Stadium so great, I realized after a visit
last week, is the carnival atmosphere outside the park....
</P>
<P>
   But enough about the 3-year-olds, all my nonracing friends are
saying after the Belmont Stakes excitement. Tell us more about the
fillies-on-turf division!...
</P>
<P>
   Tennis is celebrating this week. The French Open TV rating was
nearly half that of the Belmont.
</P>
<P>
   If only tennis could produce some good young players, then it
might be interesting again....
</P>
<P>
   Knowing how Sports Illustrated works, now that the magazine has
done a story on the sportswriting Vecsey brothers, a
Vecsey-brothers video can't be far behind. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
